Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: John the Ripper shows "No password hashes loaded"

Solution: Verify hash format matches file content. Use --list=formats to check available formats.
Issue: Hashcat shows "No devices found"

Solution: Hashcat prefers GPU but can use CPU. Add --force flag for CPU-only mode: hashcat --force -m 0 ...
Issue: Python script fails with "command not found"

Solution: Ensure full path to tools or verify they're in PATH. Use which john and which hashcat to verify.
Issue: Wordlist attack finds no passwords

Solution: Try rule-based attacks or create better wordlist. Common passwords: password, 123456, admin, test, hello.
Issue: Extraction script finds no hashes

Solution: Check regex pattern matches your LSA dump format. Verify file encoding is UTF-8.
